### Set

Set a `the_header` hook with named function as the ID:

~~~ .php
function do_set_header() {
    echo '<meta name="generator" content="Mecha">';
}

Hook::set('the_header', 'do_set_header');
~~~

Set a `the_header` hook with anonymous function:

~~~ .php
Hook::set('the_header', function() {
    echo '<meta name="generator" content="Mecha">';
});
~~~

Using custom priority:

~~~ .php
function do_set_header() {
    echo '<meta name="generator" content="Mecha">';
}

Hook::set('the_header', 'do_set_header', 1);
~~~

`1` is the function execution priority. The smaller the value, the earlier the function will be executed. And functions with the same priority are executed in the order in which they were added to the hook. Default is `10`.

### Get

Get all of the attached hooks:

~~~ .php
__dump__(Hook::get());
~~~

Get all of the attached `the_header` hooks:

~~~ .php
__dump__(Hook::get('the_header'));
~~~

### Reset

Remove an attached `the_header` hook with ID `do_set_header` before execution, or prevent a `the_header` hook with ID `do_set_header` to be attached:

~~~ .php
Hook::reset('the_header', 'do_set_header');
~~~

{{block.note}}
You cannot remove hooks that are attached using anonymous function because they have no ID.
{{/block}}

### Exist

Check for the added hooks:

~~~ .php
__dump__(Hook::set());
~~~

Check for the added `the_header` hooks:

~~~ .php
__dump__(Hook::set('the_header'));
~~~

Check if `do_set_header` is exists in the `the_header` hook:

~~~ .php
__dump__(Hook::set('the_header', 'do_set_header'));
~~~

### Fire

Execute the `the_header` hook:

~~~ .php
Hook::fire('the_header'); // → `<meta name="generator" content="Mecha">`
~~~

